  <brief_title>A Comparison of Emtricitabine and Stavudine Used With Didanosine Plus Efavirenz in HIV-Infected Patients Who Have Not Taken Anti-HIV Drugs</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Randomized, Double-Blind, Equivalence Trial Comparing Emtricitabine to Stavudine Within a Triple Drug Combination Containing Didanosine Plus Efavirenz in Antiretroviral-Drug Naive HIV-1 Infected Patients</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Triangle Pharmaceuticals</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>NIH AIDS Clinical Trials Information Service</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the safety and effectiveness of emtricitabine and
      stavudine when given with didanosine plus efavirenz to HIV-infected patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
